CORPORATE OFFICE 37 North Valley Road, Building 4, P.O. Box 1764, PAOLI, PA 19301-0801
Contact: William J. Burke (610) 889-5249
Paoli, PA, January 25, 2008  AMETEK, Inc. (NYSE: AME) today announced that its Board of Directors has increased the authorized level for repurchases of its common stock by $50 million. This increased authorization will be added to the approximately $26 million that remains available from an existing $50 million authorization approved by the Board of Directors in March 2003. Today's action brings the total amount authorized for share repurchases to approximately $76 million.
Frank S. Hermance, AMETEK's Chairman and Chief Executive Officer said, "With this increased authorization, AMETEK will continue its strategy of making opportunistic purchases of its common stock to offset the dilutive impact of our benefit plans. We will continue to allocate our strong free cash flow towards strategic acquisitions and, in their absence, debt reduction. Stock repurchases will remain a modest use of that free cash flow."
In 2007 the Company repurchased approximately 144,000 shares of its common stock for a total cost of approximately $5.4 million. The Company has not repurchased any common stock during 2008.
